main event: Observers sighted 15 to 17 objects that seemed to be in the form of eclipsing from north to south. The objects looked like flying saucers shining like stars with tails of comets.
interesting points: The objects were moving at high speeds and were observed by a duty officer and an outlookat.
The objects were visible for about 69 seconds before disappearing.
The sighting occurred in the Atlantic ocean at the coordinates 24°43'N, 55°8'W.
The report indicates that the sighting was the result of the destruction of Satellite 520, 1962 BMAD-6 (Reentry of Agent).
The report was classified as 'Other (SATELLITE DECAY)' in the conclusion.
